  <h1>Scrambled Eggs</h1>

  <p>Scrambled eggs are a classic breakfast stapleâ€”simple, satisfying, and endlessly customizable. This recipe gives you soft, fluffy eggs in minutes.</p>

  <h2>Ingredients</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>3 large eggs</li>
    <li>2 tablespoons milk</li>
    <li>Salt to taste</li>
    <li>1 tablespoon butter</li>
    <li>Freshly ground black pepper</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Instructions</h2>
  <ol>
    <li>Crack the eggs into a bowl and add milk, salt, and pepper.</li>
    <li>Whisk until the mixture is smooth and slightly frothy.</li>
    <li>Heat butter in a nonstick pan over medium-low heat.</li>
    <li>Pour in the egg mixture and let it sit for a few seconds.</li>
    <li>Gently stir with a spatula until curds form and eggs are just set.</li>
  </ol>

